                <h2>General Rental Information</h2>
                <h3>Important Documents</h3>
                <p>The renter and all drivers must have a valid original driver's license which needs to be
                    presented at
                    time of the rental. All drivers with a non-US driver's license must produce a valid Passport or a
                    valid
                    government-issued ID card as a secondary form of ID at the time of pickup.</p>
                <p>For driving the vehicle groups FVAR and PVAR German customers need to provide the class D1
                    driver's
                    license. European Citizen are allowed to drive vehicles with up to 8 seats only.<br>
                </p>
                <p>Driver's license printed with non Roman Alphabet (Arabic, Chinese, Japanese, Cyrillic etc) must
                    be
                    complemented by an international driver's license. For driver's licenses from countries not part of
                    the
                    international driver's license treaty, an official translation of the license must be presented with
                    the
                    original license.<br>
                </p>
                <h3>Age Restrictions
                </h3>
                <p>Certain regulations apply related to minimum age and possession of driver's license.</p>
                <h3>American Disabilities Act
                </h3>
                <p>Sixt offers a range of possibilities to accommodate customers with disabilities to ensure that
                    they
                    enjoy the high standard of customer service that Sixt provides.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <a name="paymentInformation"></a>
                <h2>Payment Information
                </h2>
                <h3>In General
                </h3>
                <p>We accept all major credit cards including American Express, Diners Club, Eurocard/MasterCard,
                    Discover, Visa and Airplus. The renter must be the owner of the presented means of payment which
                    must be
                    presented at the start of the rental. A valid credit card must provide available credit . <br>
                </p>
                <p>Debit cards with available funds may be accepted at most Sixt locations with two forms of
                    government-issued ID, and only if one of the following conditions are met: <br>
                    (1) The renter presents a return airline ticket or roundtrip itinerary upon pick-up. OR <br>
                    (2) An original utility bill or bank statement is presented which matches the name and address on
                    the
                    Drivers
                    License of the renter. Photocopies, printouts, and digital images are not permitted. Debit cards are
                    not
                    accepted for certain specialty vehicles and for long term rentals (defined as 28 days or longer).
                    Local
                    renters
                    cannot rent any specialty and larger vehicles with a debit card.</p>
                <p>We do not accept any Prepaid Cards, Visa Electron Cards, Electronic Use Only Cards, Maestro
                    Cards,
                    checks or Cash .<br>
                </p>
                <p>The amount that will be debited includes the rental price as well as all additional charges and
                    extras. <br>
                </p>
                <p>In generell a deposit of minimum of $100 but up to three times the hire price is charged to the
                    chosen means of payment as a security. For Debit Cards a deposit of $250 plus the cost of the rental
                    will be
                    taken as a deposit from the Debit Card. The exact deposit for high value vehicles is determined on
                    collection as
                    the amount depends on the type of vehicle driven. These funds will not be available to you during
                    the
                    rental.<br>
                </p>
                <h3>Prepaid Reservation Policies</h3>
                <p>By booking a prepaid rate, the payment will be charged before the start of rental with the
                    estimated
                    total amount of the rental (rental charge plus any other agreed charges and taxes for the full
                    agreed rental
                    period). The driver and method of payment shall be finalised at the time of reservation and cannot
                    be
                    changed. A
                    refund shall not be issued for non-collection, vehicle being collected late or returned early.<br>
                </p>
                <p>A prepaid booking can be changed up to 48 hours before the start of the rental (depending on
                    availability). An alteration fee applies. Any payment already made towards the rental will not be
                    refunded;
                    nor
                    shall any differential amount be refunded if this alteration leads to a lesser rental cost.<br>
                </p>
                <p>A prepaid booking can be cancelled before the start of the rental. In the event of a
                    cancellation,
                    any refund of the payment made towards the rental is subject to a cancellation fee. The cancellation
                    fee
                    shall
                    be the maximum amount of the first three days of the total prepaid amount. Cancellations can be made
                    online
                    or
                    in writing and must be addressed to:<br>
                </p>
                <p>Sixt Rent a Car LLC, P.O. Box 46096, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33346-0967, USA / E-Mail:
                    reservations-usa@sixt.com<br>
                </p>
                <p>In the event that the booked vehicle is not collected or not collected at the agreed time, the
                    rental
                    charge already paid shall be withheld in full.<br>
                </p>
            </div>
