                <a name="protectionConditions"></a>
                <h2>Protection Conditions
                </h2>
                <h3>Supplemental Liability Insurance
                </h3>
                <p>Liability coverage is limited to the minimum financial responsibility required by state law.<br>
                </p>
                <p>If purchased, Supplemental Liability Insurance (SLI) protects the renter against claims made by a
                    third party for bodily injury and/or property damages sustained as a result of an accident while the
                    renter
                    is
                    operating a rental vehicle.<br>
                </p>
                <p>This coverage supplies the renter with third-party liability protection up to a limit of USD
                    1,000,000 per accident.<br>
                </p>
                <p>SLI does not cover all situations that may arise while operating a rental vehicle. SLI does not
                    cover
                    all risks. There may be exclusions for unauthorized or intoxicated drivers, no first party uninsured
                    motorist
                    coverage, no coverage for certain passengers in the vehicle, and other exclusions.<br>
                </p>
                <p>For further details, see the jacket of our rental agreement and find a complete copy of the
                    Supplemental Liability Excess Policy, which is available at the counter for your review upon
                    request.<br>
                </p>
                <h3>Partial Damage Waiver
                </h3>
                <p>The Partial Damage Waiver removes the renter's responsibility for the first USD 500.00 of damage
                    to
                    or loss of the vehicle.<br>
                    The customer will be held liable for any damage or loss exceeding the amount of USD 500.00.<br>
                </p>
                <p>For further details please see the jacket of the rental agreement. Partial Damage Waiver is not
                    available in all states.<br>
                </p>
                <h3>Loss Damage Waiver </h3>
                <p>Loss Damage Waiver removes the drivers responsibility to a part of the vehicle in case of damage
                    or
                    theft.</p>
                <p>If Loss Damage Waiver is accepted, the renter is only responsible for the following amounts: <br>
                    USD 0.00 for all car groups</p>
                <p>If Loss Damage Waiver is not accepted the customer will be held liable for the full value of the
                    car.</p>
                <p>For further details please see the jacket of the rental agreement.<br>
                </p>
                <h3>Personal Accident Protection
                </h3>
                <p>Personal Accident Proctection - covers bodily injury to occupants of the rental vehicle.<br>
                </p>
                <p>Personal Accident Protection does not cover all risks. There may be exclusions.<br>
                    For further details see the jacket of our rental agreement and find a complete copy of the Personal
                    Accident
                    Insurance Policy available for your review upon request.<br>
                </p>
                <h3">Extended Roadside Protection (BC)</h3>
                <p>Sixt will provide any renter who has purchased the optional Extended Roadside Protection coverage
                    with 24/7 breakdown assistance (where available) without any additional charge. It protects the
                    renter at
                    home
                    and abroad against high service and repair costs for the following incidents:</p>
                <p>1) Key lockout service: If a renter experiences locking of the keys or key fob inside the vehicle
                    during their rental period, Sixt will cover the cost of a lockout service, by either the vehicle
                    manufacturer or
                    a 3rd party service provider, cost of delivering a new vehicle or towing of the vehicle to the
                    nearest Sixt
                    location.</p>
                <p>2) Lost key or key fob: If a renter experiences a lost or misplaced key or key fob during their
                    rental period, Sixt will cover the cost of replacing the key or key fob, cost of delivering a new
                    set of
                    keys
                    (if available), towing of the vehicle to the nearest Sixt location and for a replacement
                    vehicle.</p>
                <p>3) Flat tire service: If a renter experiences a flat tire during their rental period due to a
                    puncture, Sixt will cover the cost of repairing or replacing the tire, cost of delivering a new
                    vehicle,
                    towing
                    of the vehicle to the nearest Sixt location. Damages caused by collision will not be covered, please
                    see
                    Loss
                    Damage Waiver.</p>
                <p>4) Dead Battery: If a renter experiences a situation during their rental period, Sixt will cover
                    the
                    cost of jumpstart service, by either the vehicle manufacturer or a 3rd party service provider, cost
                    of
                    delivering a new vehicle or towing of the vehicle to the nearest Sixt location.</p>
                <p>5) Towing: If a renter experiences a mechanical failure of the vehicle during their rental
                    period,
                    Sixt will cover the cost of towing, by either the vehicle manufacturer or a 3rd party service
                    provider, cost
                    of
                    delivering a new vehicle or towing of the vehicle to the nearest Sixt location. Damages caused by
                    collision
                    will
                    not be covered, please see Loss Damage Waiver.</p>
                <p>6) Breakdown caused by empty fuel tank: If a renter experiences a breakdown due to running out of
                    fuel, Sixt will cover the costs for breakdown assistance and fuel required to continue your
                    trip.</p>
                <p>When deciding whether to purchase Extended Roadside Protection, it is recommended renters check
                    whether they have this coverage available through your personal auto insurance carrier or through a
                    3rd
                    party
                    carrier. The Extended Roadside Protection is not an insurance.</p>
                <p>All services may only be ordered by a direct claim with Sixt 24-hour Roadside Protection. Sixt
                    will
                    determine the type and extent of service required to ensure the renter stays mobile. If any damage
                    to the
                    rental
                    vehicle occurs which is not covered by Sixt within the scope of the Extended Roadside Protection,
                    the renter
                    is
                    liable for such damage.</p>
